# Semgrep ignore for antcolony.
#
# Path-traversal rules in particular are written for web handlers (Actix,
# Axum, etc.) and fire as false positives on developer CLI binaries that
# are SUPPOSED to take file paths from operator args.
#
# Scope exclusions narrowly — this file should NOT be used to silence
# real findings in the simulation or game crates.

# Developer CLI binaries — operator-typed file paths are by design.
crates/antcolony-sim/src/bin/
**/src/bin/
**/bin/

# Developer trainer crate — local CLI training tool, paths come from
# operator flags (e.g. --start mlp_weights.json). The path-traversal
# rules assume web-handler input and fire as false positives here.
crates/antcolony-trainer/

# Headless examples / harnesses — same reason.
crates/antcolony-sim/examples/
**/examples/

# Test files — test fixtures intentionally exercise edge inputs.
crates/*/tests/
**/tests/
tests/

# Build artifacts / generated.
target/
bench/
